quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  3,78,"And indeed, of them is a group who twist their tongues with the Scripture, that you<sup>pl </sup>may think it from the Scripture while it is not from the Scripture. And they say, “It is from Allah,” while it is not from Allah. And they tell lies against Allah, though they know."
  3,79,"No person to whom Allah has given the Scripture and wise judgment and prophethood would ever say to mankind, “Be my servants apart from Allah.” Rather, “Be godly{1}on account of the Scripture which you<sup>pl </sup>used to teach{2}and on account of what you used to learn.”",footnotes:1:[Literally ‘Lordly’.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: All except for Ibn Amer, Asem, Hamza, Al Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…used to know and…”]
  3,80,"Nor would he command you to take the angels and the prophets as lords. Would he command you to denial after you became Muslims{1}?",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Muslimoonwhich means those who willingly submit to God, regardless of which prophet they followed.
  3,81,"And recall when Allah took the pledge of the<i>(followers of the) </i>prophets, “Inasmuch as I{1}have given you<sup>pl </sup>of scripture and wisdom, should a messengercometo you confirming what you have, you shall certainly believe in him and you shall certainly support him.” He said, “Have you consented and taken up that heavy load towards Me upon yourselves?” They said, “We have consented.” He said, “Then bear witness, and I am with you among the witnesses.”",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Nafie’ and Abu Ja’far read it as: “Inasmuch as We have given you…” Hamza read it as: “Because of what I have given you of scripture and wisdom, then a messenger has come to you...”
  3,82,"So whoever turns away after that—those are the defiantly disobedient."
  3,83,"Do they{1}seekother than the religion of Allah, when to Him has submitted whoever is in the heavens and the earth, willingly and reluctantly, and to Him they will be returned{2}?",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: All except for Abu Amr, Hafs and Ya’qub read it as: “Do you<sup><small>pl</small></sup> seek…”],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “and to Him they return.” All except for Hafs and Ya’qub read it as: “and to Him you<sup><small>pl</small></sup> return.”]
